Certainly! Here is some example code for space vector modulation using TMS28377:

```
// Define variables for space vector modulation

float theta; // Phase angle
float Va, Vb; // Phase voltages
float Vdc; // DC bus voltage
float Vref; // Reference voltage
float Ta, Tb; // Phase duty cycles
float T1, T2, T0; // Time durations for switching 3 phases

// Calculate space vector modulated duty cycles

theta = atan2(Vb, Va); // Calculate the phase angle
Vref = sqrt(Va * Va + Vb * Vb) / sqrt(2); // Calculate the reference voltage
Ta = (Vref * cos(theta) + Vdc / 2) / Vdc; // Calculate duty cycle for phase A
Tb = (Vref * sin(theta) + Vdc / 2) / Vdc; // Calculate duty cycle for phase B
T1 = (Ta - Tb + 1) / 2; // Calculate duration for high state of Phase A
T2 = (Tb - Ta + 1) / 2; // Calculate duration for high state of Phase B
T0 = 1 - T1 - T2; // Calculate duration for high state of Phase C

// Space vector commutation code

GpioDataRegs.GPACLEAR.bit.GPIO32 = 1; // Disable Phase A
GpioDataRegs.GPACLEAR.bit.GPIO33 = 1; // Disable Phase B

if (T1 > 0.5) {
    GpioDataRegs.GPASET.bit.GPIO34 = 1; // Enable Phase A high state
} else {
    GpioDataRegs.GPACLEAR.bit.GPIO34 = 1; // Disable Phase A high state
}
if (T2 > 0.5) {
    GpioDataRegs.GPASET.bit.GPIO35 = 1; // Enable Phase B high state
} else {
    GpioDataRegs.GPACLEAR.bit.GPIO35 = 1; // Disable Phase B high state
}

if (T0 > 0.5) {
    GpioDataRegs.GPASET.bit.GPIO32 = 1; // Enable Phase C high state
} else {
    GpioDataRegs.GPACLEAR.bit.GPIO32 = 1; // Disable Phase C high state
}

```

In the above code, the main steps for space vector modulation and space vector commutation are demonstrated. The space vector modulation equations are used to calculate the duty cycles for the three phases based on the reference voltage and phase angle. The duty cycles are then used to calculate how long each phase switch must remain on. The final step is to use these time durations to drive the GPIO pins that control the FET switches in a three-phase inverter. 

Note that the specific GPIO pin assignments and configuration may need to be adjusted based on the specific implementation of the three-phase inverter.
